verbs.description: overflourish (third-person singular simple present overflourishes, present participle overflourishing, simple past and past participle overflourished)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To make excessive display or flourish of.
examples: Men, like falle Glasses, generally represent their Complexion better than Nature has made it. And as they are likely to overflourish their own Case, ſo their Flattery is hardest to be discover'd .

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To embellish with outward ornaments or flourishes; to varnish over.
